    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Areas of dry or relatively dry land or islands surrounded by water or low wetland; island groups considered archipelagos are characterized by compactness and adjacency. The original Greek meaning referred to the water in which such islands were located. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
